<HL>
   Loral Wins Air Force Contract
</HL>
<DATE>
07/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   LOR MD
</CO>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Loral Corp. was given a $71.5 million Air
Force contract for development and operation of air
crew-training systems for MC-130 aircraft.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   McDonnell Douglas Missile Systems Co., a unit of McDonnell
Douglas Corp., was issued an $18.5 million combined contract
for engineering of the Tomahawk weapon system.
</TEXT>
